77 // 1. Enable ENABLE_BISECT_TOOL below.
78 // 2. Make a new script `tmp.sh` calling a failing replay:
79 // python tests/run_replay_tests.py --filter stellar --frame 40000 --extra_args="-replay-fail-assert-instant -test-bisect $1"
80 // 3. Run the bisect script (may need to increase the end range up to 100000 or more):
81 // bash ~/tools/find-first-fail.sh -s 0 -e 1000 -v -q bash tmp.sh
82 // 4. For the number given, set `-test-bisect` to that, and set a breakpoint
83 // where specified in bisect_tool_should_skip. Whatever block being processed is the one to focus on.
84 // #define ENABLE_BISECT_TOOL

90 // Skip the first x calls.
91 bool skip = 0 <= c && c < x;
92 c++;
93 if (!skip)
94 // Set a breakpoint here.
95 x = x;
96 return skip;
97 #else
98 17825081 return false;
99 #endif
